://www.vanityfair.com/style/2022/06/bill-cosby-found-guilty-sexual-assault-lawsuit-16-year-old-playboy-mansion-1975-pay-fine#:~:text=Crime-,Bill%20Cosby%20Found%20Liable%20in%20the%20Sexual%20Assault%20of%20a,pay%20%24500%2C000%20in%20compensatory%20damages.&amp;text=A%20California%20civil%20jury%20found,was%20just%2016%20years%20old." target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>《名利场</em></a>》）。</p><p>科斯比否认了这些指控。索赔人获得 500,000 美元赔偿。</p><p><strong>如需有关英国性骚扰、攻击和强奸的帮助、建议或更多信息，请访问<a href="https://rapecrisis.org.uk/find-a-centre/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">强奸危机慈善网站</a>。在美国，请访问<a href="https://www.rainn.org/index.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RAINN</a> 。</strong></p><p>比尔·科斯比<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/bill-cosby-faces-new-lawsuit-accusing-him-of-rape-in-1972-3507281">(Bill Cosby) 面临新的诉讼，指控他在 1972 年强奸，这篇文章</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ;
夏奇拉认为人工智能“很难”模仿她https://www.nme.com/news/music/shakira-thinks-its-going-to-be-hard-for-ai-to-imitate-her-3507290?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=shakira-thinks-人工智能将很难模仿她Emma WilkesSun, 01 Oct 2023 10:49:16 +0000 Music NewsNewsPop https://www.nme.com/?p=3507290 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="夏奇拉" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “我认为他们还没有做对。我在那里听不到自己的声音”</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/shakira-thinks-its-going-to-be-hard-for-ai-to-imitate-her-3507290">夏奇拉认为人工智能“很难”模仿她的</a>帖子首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="夏奇拉" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/john-nacion-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/shakira">夏奇拉</a>分享了她对人工智能的看法，强调了该技术在尝试复制歌手声音时仍然犯的错误。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/the-movies-blog/shakira-el-dorado-world-tour-interview-2574389">夏奇拉在黑暗的日子里，愤怒的诗歌和埃尔多拉多之旅的反弹</a></strong></li></ul><p>因此，这位流行歌星认为人工智能“很难”模仿她。</p><p> “有人向我展示了我用人工智能发出的声音。但我认为他们还没有做对。我在那里听不到自己的声音，”她在一次新的采访中（通过<a href="https://www.music-news.com/news/UK/164939/Shakira-It-s-going-to-be-hard-for-AI-to-imitate-me" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>MusicNews</em></a> ）告诉<a href="https://www.billboard.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Billboard</em></a> 。</p><p> “例如，字母 E 听起来像我的声音，但其他四个元音却不是，”她继续说道。 “我认为人工智能很难模仿我。我现在还有更大的鱼要煎。</p><p> “我最关心的是弄清楚米兰[她的儿子]如何能够在同一周内练习美式橄榄球、足球和棒球，”她开玩笑地说。 </p><figure id="attachment_3507302" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3507302" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3507302" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/shakira-mike-coppola-1.jpg" alt="夏奇拉" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/shakira-mike-coppola-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/shakira-mike-coppola-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/shakira-mike-coppola-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/shakira-mike-coppola-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/shakira-mike-coppola-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/shakira-mike-coppola-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3507302" class="wp-caption-text">夏奇拉。图片来源：迈克·科波拉/盖蒂</figcaption></figure><p>人工智能在艺术创作中的运用仍然是整个 2023 年的热门话题。</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists.the-rolling-stones">滚石乐队</a>吉他手<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/keith-richards">基思·理查兹</a>最近也分享了他对人工智能的看法，称人工智能是<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-rolling-stones-says-using-ai-in-music-is-like-toy-town-3505948">“玩具城”的一部分</a>。</p><p> “人工智能就像其他任何东西一样。它可以是一个工具，也可以是一个玩具。大多数时候，所有这些东西都变成了玩具。但这就像你如何使用它，”他说。</p><p>与此同时， <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nirvana">Nirvana</a>的 Krist Novoselic <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nirvana-interview-krist-novoselic-in-utero-30-years-ai-music-new-reunion-3501830">在接受<em>NME</em>采访时</a>讨论了如何使用人工智能来完成老歌的“草图”。</p><p> “我对那里的现场表演感到很兴奋，因为他们使用了人工智能。我们从罗马、西雅图和洛杉矶的音板上获取了数字录音带，然后人工智能可以分离所有乐器，我们从中得到了非常好的混音，”他在谈到 Nirvana 开创性专辑 30 周年再版时说道&#39;在子宫内&#39;。</p><p>本周早些时候， <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/spotify">Spotify</a>创始人 Daniel Ek 透露，该公司<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-will-not-ban-music-made-by-ai-says-boss-daniel-ek-3504354">不会禁止该平台上人工智能生成的音乐</a>。</p><p>公开反对人工智能的艺术家包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/hozier">Hozier</a> （他曾考虑<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/hozier-says-he-would-consider-striking-over-ais-threat-to-music-3484663">罢工以示抗议</a>）、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/noel-gallagher">Noel Gallagher</a> （他称假<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/oasis">绿洲</a>专辑的创作者为<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/noel-gallagher-responds-to-the-ai-generated-lost-oasis-album-3451406">“该死的白痴”</a> ）和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nick-cave">Nick Cave</a> （他将其描述为<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-calls-chatgpt-and-ai-songwriting-a-grotesque-mockery-of-what-it-is-to-be-human-3381620">“对它的东西的怪诞嘲弄”）。就是成为人”</a> ）。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/shakira-thinks-its-going-to-be-hard-for-ai-to-imitate-her-3507290">夏奇拉认为人工智能“很难”模仿她的</a>帖子首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
